00:36:44.700 --> 00:36:48.260
Nat Turner's skull was recently
turned over to the family.

00:36:48.260 --> 00:36:51.420
They're doing forensic testing
on it right now to find out,

00:36:51.420 --> 00:36:54.720
and the family wants to do
a particular burial for him.

00:36:54.720 --> 00:36:56.650 position:56%
So this is not a history that's old.

00:36:56.650 --> 00:36:57.950
It's still here.

00:36:57.950 --> 00:37:01.790
This is a newspaper ad about
the bones and the remains

00:37:01.790 --> 00:37:05.390
from Virginia Commonwealth
University that I mentioned.

00:37:05.390 --> 00:37:08.030
So we are still dealing with
this history, and I would love

00:37:08.030 --> 00:37:11.120
to have conversation about
anything I've talked about,

00:37:11.120 --> 00:37:13.410
including the contemporary
ramifications

00:37:13.410 --> 00:37:14.710
of this history as well.

00:37:14.710 --> 00:37:24.920
And there's a microphone
circulating for Q&amp;A.

00:37:24.920 --> 00:37:26.770
Over here, yeah.

